p.-text
  | Buttons are used to trigger actions in forms, modals, and more.

h3 Button tags
p.-text
  | To render a button, use the tag <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code>.
  | The <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code> emits a custom event that you can listen to, the event name is <code>chiClick</code>
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3.-d--flex
    each type in ['Button', 'Link', 'Input', 'Submit', 'Reset']
      div.-pr--2
        chi-button()
          span=type
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button>Button</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Link</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Input</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Submit</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Reset</chi-button>

h3 Examples

h4 Base
p.-text
  | Chi includes a wide variety of predefined button styles. For most cases,
  | the base and <code>primary</code> buttons will be sufficient. For special cases,
  | such as styling a destructive action button, a <code>danger</code> button may be used.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3.-d--flex
    each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Secondary:'secondary', Danger:'danger', Dark:'dark'}
      div.-pr--2
        chi-button(color=type)
          span=val
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary'>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='secondary'>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='danger'>Danger</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='dark'>Dark</chi-button>

h4 Outline
p.-text
  | To remove a buttons solid background and keep its colored border, apply the attribute
  | <code>outline</code> on the <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code> tag.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3.-d--flex
    each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Secondary:'secondary', Danger:'danger', Dark:'dark'}
      div.-pr--2
        chi-button(color=type, outline)
          span=val
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button outline>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary' outline>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='secondary' outline>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='danger' outline>Danger</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='dark' outline>Dark</chi-button>

h4 Flat
p.-text
  | To render a button with a transparent background and border, set the attribute <code>type</code> value to
  | <code>flat</code> on the <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code> tag.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3.-d--flex
    each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Secondary:'secondary', Danger:'danger', Dark:'dark'}
      div.-pr--2
        chi-button(color=type, flat)
          span=val
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button flat>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary' flat>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='secondary' flat>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='danger' flat>Danger</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='dark' flat>Dark</chi-button>

h3 Pill
p.-text To render buttons with a more pronounced border-radius, set the attribute <code>type</code> value to
  | <code>pill</code> on the <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code> tag..
h4 Base
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3.-d--flex
    each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Secondary:'secondary', Danger:'danger', Dark:'dark'}
      div.-pr--2
        chi-button(color=type, type='pill')
          span=val
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button type='pill'>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary' type='pill'>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='secondary' type='pill'>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='danger' type='pill'>Danger</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='dark' type='pill'>Dark</chi-button>

h3 Fluid
p.-text Buttons can be expanded to fill the parent space by applying the attribute
  | <code>fluid</code> on the <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code> tag.
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3
    each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Secondary:'secondary', Danger:'danger', Dark:'dark'}
      div.-pt--2
        chi-button(color=type, fluid)
          span=val
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button fluid>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary' fluid>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='secondary' fluid>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='danger' fluid>Danger</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='dark' fluid>Dark</chi-button>

h4 Outline
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3.-d--flex
    each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Secondary:'secondary', Danger:'danger', Dark:'dark'}
      div.-pr--2
        chi-button(color=type, outline, type='pill')
          span=val
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button type='pill' outline>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary' type='pill' outline>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='secondary' type='pill' outline>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='danger' type='pill' outline>Danger</chi-button>
